did.unittitle: Central Washington University Office of Alumni Relations, Memorabilia
did.abstract: The Alumni Relations Memorabilia collection features a variety of trophies, athletics gear, ceramics, glassware, clothing, and other items representative of Central Washington University’s history from the 1890s to 2013.

phystech.p: Textiles, commemorative objects, trophies, plaques, metal objects, athletics gear, and glassware in fair condition, with aging to older materials

bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: The doors of the Washington State Normal School in Ellensburg opened in 1891. Mr. Benjamin Franklin Barge was the first principal of the school, which was founded to educate future elementary and junior high teachers. Classes were held at the Washington Public School until the normal school's first building, Barge Hall, opened in 1893. The normal school became Central Washington College of Education in 1937, Central Washington State College in 1961, and Central Washington University in 1977.

Founded in 1944, Central Washington University's Alumni Association provides opportunities for the continued connection between alumni and Central Washington University. The Alumni Association manages events and activities throughout the year, including reunions, homecoming, annual fundraising, Alumni Association scholarships and Distinguished Alumni Awards, Board meetings and workshops, the Central advisor program, tennis clinics, and miscellaneous gatherings.

scopecontent.p: The Alumni Relations collection features a variety of trophies, athletics gear, glassware, clothing, and other items representative of Central Washington University’s history from the 1890s to 2013. Notable are athletics items, including signed Dan Murphy and Dave Heaverlo jerseys.

arrangement.p: Items will be added to series as accessioned

accessrestrict.p: Open to the public for educational research

relatedmaterial.p: Materials related to the Alumni Relations collection may be found in the Athletic Department—-Team Sports collection. The athletics collection should be consulted for specifics about athletes and competitions.
